Title: Envelope Addressed to Vida Chenoweth from David Woodcock
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: This is a big brown envelope sent from David Woodcock to Vida Chenoweth at an address in Auckland. The envelope is undated and and contains no letter inside.

Title: Printed Email from Jennifer Dieffenbach to Virginia Whitney
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: This email seems to be sent at the request of a Dr. Hsu, who wanted to provide Chenoweth with a list of marimba music by a composer named Harry Donald Hewitt. The email contains the list of such music.

Title: Letter from Jorge Sarmientos to Mederic Fitzpatrick, Dec. 15th, 1963
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: A manilla folder containing the original handwritten letter, a digitally typed translation of the letter, and a typewriter-typed copy of what seems to be program notes about a piece called "Cinco Estampas Cakchiqueles Descriptivas para Orquestra". The original letter seems to have accompanied these program notes.

Title: Letter from Eugene J. Ulrich to James L. Moore, October 28, 2005
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: In this letter, Ulrich enclosed his solo marimba arrangements of the Bach Chorales "Come, Sweet Death" and "O Sacred Head"(5.6.43 and 5.6.44). He discusses the origin and playing of these pieces, particularly Chenoweth's involvement with them and with the instrument itself. He also discusses errors In a printing of his Suite No.1 for marimba.

Title: Letter from Eugene J. Ulrich to Vida Chenoweth, not dated
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: In this letter, Ulrich sends Chenoweth copies of a number of his pieces, and requests that Chenoweth send him any recordings of her playing the enclosed pieces that she might have. The letter is not dated.

Title: Envelope "2 CD's of Bee + Chenoweth"
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: Written on the cover of this folder is: "2 CD's of Bee + Chenoweth #I Vida and Darlene in N.Z. 1968 #II Vida and Darlene in P.N.G. and on furlough.....1970 Vida's tour w Marimba Hawaii" Despite this, there are no CD's in the folder. The contents of the folder seems to be an itemized list of all the files that the CD's contain, printed on paper. It appears to have been mostly photos.

Title: Alfred Publishing Co. Royalty Report
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: A report detailing the amount of royalty that Chenoweth has earned for the 7 Bach Chorales book (5.6.14). It is enclosed in a big orange envelope, which is dated May 10th, 2010.

Title: A Festival of Fine Arts concert program
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: A program for a fine arts festival at William Woods College, held in April of 1965. The festival was five nights long and included a performance of a play, three concerts, and a lecture. The final concert on April 23rd was performed by Vida Chenoweth, in which she played many of the pieces found elsewhere in this collection.

Title: Etude
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: Two small pages of photocopied sheet music titled "Etude". The composer is listed as R. Chenoweth.

Title: The Christian Life
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: Five copied half-pages of sheet music seemingly for a hymn called The Christian Life. They are numbered strangely - page "506" extends across most of these half-pages.

Title: Untitled Sheet Music
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: Five pages of handwritten sheet music. One page has "Vida" at the top. They seem to be exercises of some sort, but it is unclear what they are actually for. They are annotated throughout. These sheets were found next to the top of a folder marked "Fugue", although its difficult to tell if they were actually inside the folder or not. Given that and also that a lot of these notes on the music seem to indicate that this was a piece being continually edited, it is possible that they were part of a fugue, but it's difficult to say definitively.

Title: Song for Pat: "Happy Birthday"
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: The title "Song for Pat" is written at the bottom of the sheet. It seems to be a handwritten setting of a bible verse (Rev.7:16,17 is written at the end of the staff). The top right of the page says "Vida June, '60"

Title: Invention
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: Sheet music for a piece titled Invention. The top right of the page says "Vida Chenoweth '51". The piece is written across two pages of sheet music which fold together like a folder.

Title: Invention (#1)
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: This seems to be a different version of the Invention piece by Chenoweth. This one is written on very thin sheet music paper and folded over at the top.

Title: Deed by Deed
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: Sheet music for a piece titled Deed by Deed, by Vida Chenoweth. An inscription on the front says "New Guinea - 1971" and also notes that the piece was "Inspired by the poem Patience by G.A. Studdard Kennedy".

Title: Allegretto Brilliante
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: The inscription on the top is difficult to read but it seems like it says "Allegretto Brilliante". It is handwritten in blue ink.

Title: Broken-Chord Etude
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: The title of this piece is "Broken-Chord" Etude, and it is marked as "Etude Opus No. 1". It is handwritten in blue ink and annotated throughout, with long instructions on the bottom of both sides of the manuscript.

Title: Four Central American Folk Tunes
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: A folder containing Chenoweth's solo marimba arrangements of four folk songs from Central America. The folder contains: "Pitos Y Tortugas" "¡Ah Que Indio!" "Tíc, La Siembra" "Las Mañanitas" as well as a paper explaining the origins of each song and giving a short professional biography of Chenoweth. The copyright on the sheets is for 1993.

Title: Untitled Photocopied sheet music
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: Two pages of untitled sheet music in a clear sleeve. The pages are somewhat annotated, with certain measures crossed out.

Title: Black Paper Sheet Music
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: Two sets of sheet music for marimba, one of them in a clear plastic sleeve. The sheet music is on black paper, with the notes written in white. They are both attributed to V. Chenoweth, but lack titles or classification.

Title: Carl Busch's Music Tablet
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: Two browning pages of untitled sheet music, handwritten in pencil. They seem to be exercises of some sort. "Carl Busch's Music Tablet" is written down the side of the sheets.

Title: Stretti, Episodes, and Canons
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: Several pages of seemingly miscellaneous sheet music. Some of the sheets are labeled, such as the second sheet which says "Stretti", and some of the sheets later in the pile, which read "Episodes" or "Canon". They are all handwritten and annotated. There is no order to them that I can discern, but they seem to go together.

Title: Marimba: 7 Bach Chorales
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: A small book of sheet music containing 7 Bach chorales in arrangements for Marimba. Chenoweth is attributed as the editor, and the book begins with a biographical page on Chenoweth, showcasing her accomplishments. This book contains the chorales: "Jesu, Joy of Man's Desiring " (of which there are two copies) "Dearest Lord Jesus, Oh Why Dost Thou Tarry?" "Beloved Jesus, What Law Hast Thou Broken?" "Jesus, I Will Ponder Now" "Out Of The Depths I Cry To Thee" "Praise God, The Lord, Ye Sons of Men" "If Thou But Suffer God To Guide Thee" Each piece is accompanied by a set of notes on how best to play the piece.

Title: A Vida Chenoweth Collection: Recently Discovered Gems for Marimba
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: This book of sheet music, featuring a picture of Chenoweth on the cover amidst a pink floral background, contains a number of Chenoweth's original compositions for Marimba. The compositions included in this book are: "Pinocchio" "Social Dances" "Chopi-Style" "Blues" "Invention No. 1 for Solo Marimba" "Invention No. 2 for Solo Marimba" "Invention for Marimba and Cello" There is a second copy of this book, but this second copy is missing its front and back covers and contains only the interior pages - although these pages are in good condition and very usable.

Title: Pointillism
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: A book of sheet music for a piece called Pointillism by Chenoweth, in which Chenoweth attempted to recreate the Pointillism technique of Georges Seurat in music. The book includes parts for Flute, Clarinet in Bb, and Marimba. It contains a staff with all three instruments parts together as well as separate parts for each individual instrument. There are also a couple other copies of this piece, in various different configurations. I have included them here with the finished booklets.

Title: Concerto for Marimba and Orchestra
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: Four black wire-bound books of sheet music containing a Concerto for Marimba and Orchestra by Robert Kurka. It is dated 1956 and dedicated to Vida Chenoweth. There are two copies of a "Piano reduction" of the score, one with damaged binding and the other in plastic wrapping and taped shut. There are also two copies of a full score of the piece in a similar arrangement - one has slightly damaged binding, and the other is wrapped in plastic.

Title: Let Not Your Heart Be Troubled
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: Sheet music for a choral piece written by Robert Chenoweth, dedicated to Vida Chenoweth. It is enclosed in a green and white first class mail envelope, addressed to Chenoweth's address in Oklahoma City. It is dated November 10, 2010.

Title: Let Not Your Heart Be Troubled, Second copy
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: A different mailed copy of the piece by Robert Chenoweth. This one is in a bright orange first class mail envelope. This copy of the sheet music is in a small pamphlet with several pages, where the other copy is on a larger, single sheet of paper. It is dated June 17th, 2010.

Title: Béla Bartók Mikrokosmos
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: A book of sheet music containing Béla Bartók's Mikrokosmos pieces for solo piano. The book of sheet music is wrapped in a copy order slip, which is dated 1997. The book contains the pieces: "Free Variations" "Subject and Reflection" "From the Diary of a Fly" "Divided Arpeggios" "Minor Seconds, Major Sevenths" "Chromatic Invention" "Ostinato" "March" "Six Dances in Bulgarian Rhythm"

Title: Series of Scrapbooks
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: A number of scrapbooks in extremely poor condition. Material would need to be extracted and re-organized.

Title: Series of letters to Isadore Goldberg from Harry Nathano
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: This letter discusses potential booking rates and plans for Betty Lee's performances.

Title: Series of letters to Isadore Goldberg from Harry Nathano
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: Letter asks questions regarding booking Betty Lee for performances in London and Australia.

Title: Series of letters to Isadore Goldberg from Harry Nathano
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: This letter discusses potential booking rates and plans for Betty Lee's performances.

Title: North American Investment and Loan Association Twelfth Annual Dinner Dance
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: Program for aforementioned dance. Contains a menu, a statement, and a listing of performers, including Betty Lee as "Girl Xylophonist Supreme".

Title: 20th Anniversary Medinah Medical Staff Dinner
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: A program and menu for a dinner event. Betty Lee is listed as a performer, "Wizard of the Xylophone". The back of the program tells a short history of the medical establishment.

Title: International Association of Printing House Craftsmen 23rd Annual Convention Banquet and Ball
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: A program and menu for this event. Betty Lee is a performer, among others.

Title: Cunard Liner Christmas Eve Revue
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: This seems to be a program for an event hosted aboard a cruise ship. "Betty Brett" xylophonist.

Title: Cunard New Year's Eve Revue Program
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: This is a program for another event on the same cruise ship, hosted a couple days after the last one. Betty Brett also performed here, under that name.

Title: Cunard After Dinner Concert Program
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: Program for a concert held on the R.M.S. Mauretania. There are a number of pieces listed that seem to be solo performances by Betty Lee.

Creator: Sam Winship
Description: Another Cunard line program, this time from the RMS Caronia. There are a number of performers, including Betty Lee.

Title: Hejaz Grotto 12 Annual Benefit Vaudeville Show
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: This is a large pamphlet for this benefit show, with a large number of donors and advertisers and photos of grotto members.

Title: Gopher Candy Club Seventh Annual Friendship Dinner
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: A large program with donors and advertisers for an event at a club for candy salesmen and craftsmen. Betty Lee performed and is listed as "Musical Bombshell".

Title: WCFL Annual Radio Frolics "Varieties of '47"
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: A large program for an event held by a labor union radio station. Features advertisements and donors, as well as a page on Betty Lee with a picture.

Title: Bermuda Cruise Pamphlet
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: A pamphlet describing different facilities and features of a cruise to Bermuda on the Holland-America Line.

Title: Au Revioir Review Program
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: A program for an event on a cruise ship, the s.s. Maasdam, a ship from the Holland-America Line, which was mentioned in the previous archive. Betty Lee performed, listed as "Betty Brett". The cover is unusual and has a beautiful illustration.

Title: Program Holland America Line
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: Another program from the Holland America Line, for a Revue at which Betty Lee performed, listed as Betty Brett.

Title: Chicago Cigar, Tobacco, and Cigarette Salesmen's Union Program
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: Contains a number of interesting advertisements. Betty Lee performed.

Title: Tam O'Shanter's First 1942 Golf Invitational Day Program
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: A large program (with a nude pin-up on the cover) for an event at a men's golf club. Betty Lee performed last, and a description indicates that she played Liszt's Hungarian Rhapsody at this event.

Title: Continental Motors Program
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: A program and menu for an event held by a car-manufacturing company. It contains a number of records of speakers, addresses, and entertainers, Betty Lee among them.

Title: Northern Lights Lodge 25th Anniversary Celebration Program
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: A program for an event at a Masonic Lodge. Betty Lee performed.

Title: King Oscar Lodge Dance and Reception Program
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: A program for a dance at which Betty lee performed with a number of other acts. There is a picture of her at the Xylophone.

Title: Van Buren Post No.401 Souvenir Program
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: This dance was held by a branch of the Chicago Post Office Union. Betty Lee is listed as a performer. The pages of the program are in fine condition, but the cover is bent and torn separate from the middle pages.

Title: Aragon Ballroom Dance Topics Section
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: What appears to be a section of a magazine devoted to dance and music related news. There is an advertisement for a ball at which Betty Lee performed. The magazine is in very poor condition and would have to be handled with care so as not to tear it further.

Title: Christmas Greetings Card
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: The card has a nice illustration and a printed note on the inside. It is hand-signed "Saluy" or maybe "Saloy". Maybe "Savoy"?

Title: Christmas Greetings Card
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: Another Christmas Card. This one is long and blue, and has the same conventions as the other, just in different proportions. It appears to be signed "Tina".

Title: Fraternity of the Graphic Arts 4th Annual Yearbook
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: This large program is from 1939, making it the oldest in the collection (so far) - in it, Betty Lee is referred to as "16 Year Old Girl Wonder Xylophonist".

Title: Variety Club of Grand Rapids Inaugural Banquet
Creator: Sam Winship
Description: A program for a 1945 banquet at which Betty Lee performed.
